    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Something I've always wished Vim had is the ability to use text objects as command ranges, so you could do:\n\n``` vim\n    :i}norm ^i// <CR>\n```\n\nto comment out lines inside a pair of curly brackets (that's a bad example, but it's the only one I could think of that doesn't use one of my user defined commands) rather than having to:\n\n``` vim\n    vi}\n    :'<,'>norm ^i// <CR>\n```\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
